headline: CoStar Group Enters Binding Agreement to Acquire Leading Australian Property Marketplace Domain Holdings
summary: ARLINGTON, Va., May 09, 2025--CoStar Group, Inc. (NASDAQ: CSGP), a leading provider of online real estate marketplaces, information, analytics and 3D digital twin technology in the property markets, announced today that it has entered a binding Scheme Implementation Deed (SID) to acquire 100% of the issued capital of Domain Holdings Australia Limited, a leading Australian property marketplace.

headline: CoStar to buy Australia's Domain in $1.9 billion deal, eyes REA's market dominance
summary: (Reuters) -U.S. real estate firm CoStar will acquire Domain for A$3 billion ($1.92 billion) including debt, the Australian property listings platform said on Friday, in a bid to create a well-capitalised rival to News Corp's REA.  After weeks of due diligence by CoStar, which owns a 16.9% stake in Domain, the companies have agreed on the U.S. firm's A$4.43 apiece offer.  Domain shares gained as much as 5.2% to A$4.47 and were set for their biggest single-day rise in nearly a month.
